<font color="#FF0000">WALL</font><br>
<tt>Thu May  1 23:14:24 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
The Wall was brought over to Maui by the local vet organization years ago. And, while it was here for about four days, I never went down to see it. First and foremost, I had a very ominous feeling about the wall, you know, like I would die there or something. Second, I knew of no names at that time, so I didn't see any point. Probably was just an excuse. <br><br>
That is not to say I would not want to go to DC sometime to see The Wall. I have this fantasy of going to the east, visiting one of my company commanders (the best I had)that I located, go visit the Wall, travel down to S. Carolina to visit the grave of my L.T. who was killed in 'Nam, and play the bagpipes a tune for him (no bagpipe jokes, please) and visit his wife before returning home.<br><br>
Still haven't been able to shake that ominous feeling, though.
